    "## 2. The question: decision, action, cost of a wrong call\n",
    "\n",
    "*What decision does your work improve? Who acts on it? What does a wrong recommendation cost?*"
    "*My provisional lane is Refresh / Content Opportunity Scoring. The search question is: which pages should editors refresh first? The unit of analysis is the page. The output is a ranked review queue with a score and reason codes. The action is for editors to review the top-ranked pages and refresh the ones most likely to need attention. A wrong recommendation wastes editor time and can leave a declining page unfixed. Data and ML can help because the relationship between signals and decline is noisy and not obvious from simple rules.*"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Decision: Which pages should editors refresh first?\n",
      "Action: Editors review the ranked queue, SEO specialists and refresh the highest-priority pages.\n",
      "Cost of a wrong call: A wrong recommendation wastes editor time on pages that do not need attention, and it can let a truly declining page stay unfixed longer.\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "decision = \"Which pages should editors refresh first?\"\n",
    "action = \"Editors review the ranked queue, SEO specialists and refresh the highest-priority pages.\"\n",
    "cost_of_wrong_call = (\n",
    "    \"A wrong recommendation wastes editor time on pages that do not need attention, \"\n",
    "    \"and it can let a truly declining page stay unfixed longer.\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Decision:\", decision)\n",
    "print(\"Action:\", action)\n",
    "print(\"Cost of a wrong call:\", cost_of_wrong_call)\n"
   ]
